agro from almost as far away as you can see them).<br><br>I always make a point of stopping at the bottom of the hill and looking around.  Wait there for a good 10-20 seconds and make sure nothing is on or near you.  Then, and only then, proceed to the camp.  This may increase the chances of a wandering mob attacking you, but wouldn't you rather make the &quot;noble sacrifice&quot; than cause the death of many many people?  I know I would...<br><br>And something else to remember: if you see someone near you get attacked, it's very likely that you are on the mobs hate list as well.  So just because something isn't attacking you YET doesn't mean it's safe for you to proceed to the camp.<br><br>And once there, for gods sake, don't sit down until the raid admin has said it's safe.  Sitting down doubles your agro range, possibly more... which added to the already long Fear mob agro range... well, you get the point. <p>-Kommisar Nils "Can-Head" Hansen -- Guild Officer. Master Smith. Tank.KCoG Dragon Liason (retired)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugenine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Genine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(4/5/02 10:52:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=248.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://216.240.138.22/images/animate/faces/anirat.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Plane of Fear recap </span><hr size=1> I just look at this as a worse case scenario. The last fear raid that I was on with you Destructress was the exact opposite as this one and we had less people. I remember Cazvoy saying something about people breaking mezzes on break-in.  I must say, I kept checking back here hoping groups were made up and I think always making groups is a great idea. You can then know everybody who you assign to the break-in groups and can announce MA and SA at the get go to avoid breaking mezzes in the future.<br><br>I will go on any and, hopefully, all raids that you run Destructress. I still had fun, even dying 7 times! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Genine Brickhaus<br>51 Shaman<br>Emerald Unity <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulagdalentarcho.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lagdalen Tarcho</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoG Companion</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(4/5/02 1:32:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=248.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Plane of Fear recap </span><hr size=1> First my appologies for not being able to come along, rl called me away.<br><br>If I may make a couple suggestions?<br><br>As you noted above, numbers make a difference. the more people you have the more PL you get and the more people go LD. A good sum to go with is 5 - 7 groups.<br><br>When you buff up to go in, no sow hehe. Unless everyone knows whats goin on and what to do, sow is a killer. So is not having invis on. Fine so there's undead and live creatures in there, put it on anyway and heaven forbid you zone without it.<br><br>When I used to go with CoG we were told, zone in, take one step foreward, turn 90 degrees left and run to the wall....... NONONONONONONONONONONO.<br>There's one little step in here that must be removed. &quot;take one step foreward&quot;. dont move an inch foreward talk about a step. (unless you want to agro another 10 creatures your way to train) Turn automatically left and then go down the hill SLOWLY. There is NO reason to rush since when you get to the bottom you'll just have to wait anyway.<br><br>And as Kommi pointed out, do NOT sit once you're there. Everyone should stand until front is broken. no mana? too bad, stand and med it up. Sitting can potentially agro another 20 creatures onto you.<br><br>I know everyone is eager for loot but I would very strongly reccomend sending in only 3 groups (of all the highest lvl people you have) to break and have everyone else wait outside. Once you break the wall, then have the others zone in 1 at a time (not all at once). As each group gets to the safe spot and are accounted for, call in the next group. This way there are less people to get stuck on top of eachother on the port in point, less people to agro mobs, and like it or not, people are much more exposed and you can tell who trained you. (if that helps any)<br><br>Hint for groups: if you have a CoH mage, always put them with the puller <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  but I'm sure you knew that.<br><br>And Destrucress, to reduce the stress on you, choose one person from each generic class type (tank, pure caster, priests) and have them deal with tells along with you. Just make sure it's someone who knows and understands the zone lol. preist questions to priest leader, pure's to pure leader, tank's to tank leader. No one person can be expected to understand how everyone's class works best even though some claim they do know. Let the tank class leader sort out who would be best MT, let the monks figure out who would be best puller. They aren't dumb, sure they want the honor but there's a difference between experience and eagerness. One gets ya pulls, one gets ya dead <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br><br>Well that was longer than I intended but hopefully there were a couple good tricks in there. Gimme a shout anytime if you need a hand or just want a friendly mage along <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><img src=http://www.myezboard.com/projects/ezboard/ezboard_userimages/valoran/images/LagSigPic.jpg <br>LvL 58 Conjurer <br>http://www.geocities.com/lag_zol/Main<TABLE BORDER=0><TR><TD><A HREF="http://blog.ravenblack.net/quiz/flavour.pl"><IMG BORDER=0 ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=100 SRC="http://blog.ravenblack.net/quiz/flavour/2.png" ALT="What Flavour Are You? I am Chocolate Flavoured." /></A>I am <B>Chocolate</B> Flavoured.<BR /><BR />I am sweet and a little bit naughty. I am one of the few clinically proven aphrodisiacs. Sometimes I can seem a little hard, but show warmth and I soon melt. <A HREF="http://blog.ravenblack.net/quiz/flavour.pl">What Flavour Are You?</A></TD></TR></TABLE></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udestructressfyrestarter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Destructress Fyrestarter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoG Companion</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(4/7/02 1:55:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=248.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Plane of Fear recap </span><hr size=1> Thank you all for your encouragement and wonderfull advice <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>we learn as we go, and leading these raids has been my biggest learning experience in EQ.<br><br>I am very pleased in general with all the peolple who have join us on our KCoG raids, and if allowed, plan to 