orting back out to ferrot and having the melees rejoin the break groups for the second run.<br><br>Mages, if avalible need to be in the first 3 groups, mod rods are invaluable during the break the more mod rods clerics and chanters can lay their hands on the better more heals more mezzing=more dead mobs<br><br>of course ideally the break groups want enchanters and clerics in all of them.<br><br>The rest of the group can be filled in with wizards, melee.<br><br>My planes career is rather short, but im 2-1 so far successful break in hate and fear and if things go well I will never get another loss<br><br>The MA and SA need to be made clear and repeated a number of times like ever 5 mins.<br><br>People need to listen, especially peeps in the break groups.<br><br>And also people need to understand that running a large pick up raid is the most aggravating experience you can endeavor to start in EQ so basically, WE DON'T WANT TO HEAR YOU MOANING, GRIPING, BITCHING, or WHINING if you don't like how its going well you know where the zone or your nearest wizard with Trans is get to it and wave goodbye. STFU<br><br>Yizelar Kontrol<br>Overlords of Darkness<br>Karana server<br>Level 58 Enchanter of Quellious <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulagdalentarcho.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lagdalen Tarcho</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoG Companion</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(4/8/02 3:47:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=248.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Plane of Fear recap </span><hr size=1> I wont say I agree with some of what you said Yiz, but some of the rest is true.<br><br>(and I know of rangers at lvl 55 having 100 less life than a lvl 60 warrior and more ac then that same warior so that wont hold true) You need the highest lvls, pure and simple. like it or not the higher the lvl the smaller the agro range, the less a creature resists stuff and the faster stuff dies (disciplines etc).<br><br>Ran, broke and participated in more planes raids then I care to count and I know what worked and what didn't <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  but at the same time I'm not going to grudge you out of trying, I'm simply stating suggestions not rules, though as advice I wouldn't say I'm far off what anyone else my lvl and experience would say. Well anyway, at least now you have idea's for next time <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukellory.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kellory</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(4/8/02 4:32:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=248.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Plane of Fear recap </span><hr size=1> Let me state first off I didnt attend this raid, nor any other KCoG plane raid since I stepped down.  The main reason behind this is I believe it will only lead to friction as people look to me as opposed to the Raid Leader for direction.<br><br>Now then.  One thing I suggest is people go back and read my Planar Raid Recaps.  They are not just lengthy and long winded recaps of who got what loot.  They contain not just lessons, but also advice and suggestions for doing things better in the future.  You can learn from the past or you can learn on your own.  Either way you gain the experience, but one way is a lot less painful than the other.<br><br>And I need to agree with Lagdalen.  The difference between a 50 warrior and a 55 Shadow Knight, or Ranger, or Rogue, or Paladin, or any other melee is extreme.  I often used a 59 SK for an MA in Fear and Hate.  I've used a 60 Ranger as well.<br><br>Group makeup is an art form as opposed to a science.  Especially in KCoG where you may or may not know who is showing up.  You need to take into account not just levels, but equipment, experience, reliability, and spell/weapon layout.  I'd rather have an experienced level 55 ranger be my MA than a level 60 Warrior from X Uber guild who has never been on a KCoG raid before.  <br><br>One thing that often makes things easier is to have a single leader.  Period.  If you have seperate leaders for different tasks then you will get confusion in the raid.  This isnt true for guilds such as Valoran or Watchmen or Grey Hawke that work in and with confusing and rapidly changing situations.  But you are dealing with people who often have no planar or large scale raid experience and knowing they can listen to a single person helps a whole lot.<br><br>When Haemish used to lead KCoG plane raids we learned the problems with one person being in charge and another running the raid itself.  KCoG was never as successful as when a single person did everything.  It simplifies the situation enourmously.<br><br>And finally, attitude among the leaders is everything.  There is a big difference between keeping control of the raid and talking down to your raiders.  I do expect those that raid with me to be quiet and no complain.  However, there are other ways of getting this accross than telling them to STFU.<br><br>The one thing a leader cannot afford at any time is to become annoyed or angry.  And even worse to show it for any reason.  It destroys morale faster than almost anything else.  When you step up to lead you must lead, not simply stand in front and be the first to die.<br><br>Kellory Silverstar<br>The Watchmen<br>KCoG Plane Raid Liason-Retired <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udreamswalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DreamsWalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(4/9/02 7:47:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=248.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Plane of Fear recap </span><hr size=1> Yes its true rangers can have hps and AC like that, but this isnt one of the uber guild raids, we have peeps that are going to the planes for the armor there.... which compared to most quest velious armors is pure junk. Low level does cause arggo, sigh but you dont get many 55-60 on a pick up raid they tend to be members of guilds that only enter the planes for epics... and god killing so they wouldnt bother with KCoG. The few we do get are ofcourse invauleable thanks Gruz <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  and all you others that come. Your advice is welcome as always Lagdalen (even though we have had our differences in the past I'm not about to say I know near enough about breaking a plane <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br><br>As for STFU well what can I say, just last fear raid we had a wizard roll for the right to hand in his cog to the golem, come to find out he didnt ever have it on him, then he left to get it and when we were clearing the area to kill the golem he decided to hand it in, no we didnt all die.... everything was ok but it could have been much worse. Then I come to find out he was in ec the next week selling all of his equipment and and leaving the game or changing characters one (not to sure) and last raid you would have to been there to understand......... so dont tell me how to act, I dont lead I assist Destructress. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uentwain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Entwain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(4/12/02 9:53:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=248.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Plane of Fear recap </span><hr size=1> That was a freakin blast.. and i luved coming in to give a hand although i kick myself in the teeth for not showing up on the initial break in (tsw raid i had no clue about), destructress you did AWESOME god it was fun doin that with you guys and draco goes down next time i see that dwaggon...<br><br>Entwain Demoshine<br><br>If I was an Autobot, I'd be:&lt;br&gt;<br><a href="http://android5.com/misc/tests"><img border=0    src="http://android5.com/misc/tests/autobot/ironhide.gif"  alt="Click to see what Autobot you could be!"></a>&lt;br&gt;<br>Take the <a href="http://android5.com/misc/tests">Transformers personality test</a> at android5.com!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;<br><br>MAGELO<br><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=165036">www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=165036</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>KCoG Founder</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(4/15/02 4:04:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=248.topic&index=12>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.godwinclients.com/sd/haemish_new.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Plane of Fear recap </span><hr size=1> I'll have to chime in with Kellory and Lagdalen here. Break-in, especially in Fear (or portal breaks in Hate) can be done with 3-4 groups of 50+ players. They actually take less time, have fewer casualties and are more fun than 6 group pileups. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>The best way to do break in on Fear is really with 3-4 groups of experienced raiders with an average level of 52-55. Not saying that someone under 50 can't be helpful, but if for nothing else than the fact that at post-50 levels, HP's, AC, mana levels, disciplines, etc. are VASTLY different. Someone more efficient than me can point to research that shows that melee characters are on a completely different damage/to-hit table than under 50 characters. Not to mention the fact that most of the creatures will con white/yellow to a 52+ as opposed to red to lower levels, and you see the benefits. <br><br>However, it can be done with 4-5 groups of 46-49th level folks. You're just going to have more deaths, probably need to evac a few times and take a bit longer. It can actually be more fun. Personally, I always LOVED being in the break-in groups, because aside from mini-boss fights, once the plane is broken, it's all just fairly simple loot-collection from there. Pull mob to camp, kill it while mezzing any adds, rinse repeat. Now doing AE multi-mob kills is a blast as well.  <p>Haemish MacLennan<br>Founder<Br>Karana Council of Guilds<br>"I don't play role-playing games to be a politician."</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showPrevMessage?topicID=248.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showNextMessage?topicID=248.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=248.topic&index=12><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.emailToFriend?topicID=248.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.threadControl?topicID=248.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=248.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=248.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub6.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="councilofguildsgeneral">General<option value="councilofguildscouncildiscussions">Council Discussions<